50|$|Tortoises share a mutualistic {{relationship}} with some species of GalÃ¡pagos finch and mockingbirds. Small groups of finches initiate {{the process by}} hopping {{on the ground in}} an exaggerated fashion facing <b>the</b> <b>tortoise.</b> <b>The</b> <b>tortoise</b> signals it is ready by rising up and extending its neck and legs, enabling the birds to reach otherwise inaccessible spots on <b>the</b> <b>tortoise's</b> body such as the neck, rear legs, cloacal opening, and skin between plastron and carapace. The birds benefit from the food source and <b>the</b> <b>tortoises</b> get rid of irritating ectoparasites.|$|R
