5|$|As, {{according}} to Bulgarian mythology {{and some other}} traditions, <b>tortoises</b> were <b>the</b> only beings who knew {{the appearance of the}} herb and the location where it grows, such people would try to obtain the raskovnik by deceiving a tortoise. They would find a tortoise nesting site and hem it in with a fence while <b>the</b> <b>tortoise</b> is away. When it returns, <b>the</b> <b>tortoise</b> would be unable to access its eggs, so it would return with a raskovnik in order to breach the fence. Thus, <b>the</b> <b>tortoise</b> would reveal <b>the</b> herb and people would acquire it from <b>the</b> <b>tortoise,</b> which does not need it anymore.|$|R
