5000|$|Daruma's {{facial hair}} is a {{symbolic}} {{representation of the}} animals well known in Asian culture to embody longevity: the crane and <b>the</b> <b>tortoise.</b> <b>The</b> eyebrows are {{in the shape of}} a crane, while the cheek hair resembles the shell of <b>the</b> <b>tortoise.</b> A Japanese-based website states that originally, there was a snake or dragon depicted across the moustache and cheeks, but was changed to <b>tortoise</b> to emphasize <b>the</b> desire for longevity. In this way, Daruma was designed to match the Japanese proverb [...] "The crane lives 1000 years, <b>the</b> <b>tortoise</b> 10,000 years".|$|R
